Explanation:

The solution iterates through the string word once using a for loop. For each character, it checks if the next character is the same and not a space. If so, it increments the count. This approach has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the word. Since the solution only uses a constant amount of space (O(1)), the space complexity is low. The energy implications are also low as the algorithm only performs a single pass through the string.

